{
  "stem": "1132.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "One of them was very close friends of my parents, and the other one was relatives, so that we knew who was moving in with us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Now, I remember the people who were friends of my parents, the man in the family was taken away in concentration camp and never returned.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "He was a dentist.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So that only women moved in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "It was his wife, his daughter, and his sister-in-law who moved in with us in the apartment.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "My family who moved in, the other room was my father's sister, husband, and two daughters.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It happens that my uncle and one of my cousins was also taken to camps, and we never again saw them again.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So that, from my immediate family, I lost an uncle and a first cousin to the camps.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Somehow or other, because my father was in that forced labor camp and he was coming and going, he was never taken away to a camp.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "To this day, I don't understand how that happened.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We-- As things got worse after '44, we saw less and less of him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But he always managed to communicate with my mother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And the reason why he managed this is because he was a survivor of World War I, and he simply knew what he had to do to do this.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "He was quite an amazing person.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I guess when you are a survivor of World War I and when you are a stowaway and you come back from Siberia and survive that, you develop an instinct of-- of what you have to do.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And that instinct kept him alive that he survived.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "As part of his survival strategy, through his friends we were able to get these protection papers, which I have one example here.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
